    <stitle>TSI 00-12-03 - T 444E Lower Thrust Main Bearing</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi001203" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>00-12-03</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>October, 2000</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engines</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>T 444E Lower Thrust Main Bearing</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>T 444E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>NEW PRODUCTION AND SERVICE LOWER THRUST MAIN BEARING</title>
                <para>A new lower thrust main bearing (#5 position only) is released for production and service in
                    International&#174; T 444E engine applications. The new bearing has been modified by removing the
                    locking tab as depicted by the illustration
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f00120301" appearance="icon">Lower Thrust Main Bearing and Main Bearing Cap
                        <xref refid="f00120301"/>.
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f00120301" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/EG8797.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="256px" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Lower Thrust Main Bearing and Main Bearing Cap</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>The new production and service bearing now affords service technicians the opportunity to install
                    and orient the lower thrust bearing in either direction. Additionally, the elimination of the
                    locking tab for the #5 main bearing lower thrust position prevents assembly interference issues with
                    the lower thrust bearing locking tab and the #5 main bearing cap. The functionality of the new
                    bearing is not impeded because it is secured by the upper bearing with locking tab.
                </para>
                <para>The remaining recommended service procedures for the main bearings and main bearing caps can be
                    found in Service Manual EGES-120.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Service bearings for lower main bearings 1 thru 4 and crankcase (upper 1-5) continue to
                            require bearings with the locking tab feature.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
